---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base title="GrooverUI — Design System">
  <div class="grooverui-page">

    <!-- ═══ HERO ═══ -->
    <div class="gv-hero">
      <img
        src="/images/work/grooverui/grooveruiheader.gif"
        alt="GrooverUI Design System — Figma library overview"
        class="gv-hero-img"
      />
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ INTRO ═══ -->
    <section class="gv-section gv-intro">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="gv-intro-headline">The foundation every feature ships from</h2>
        <p class="gv-intro-body">
          I initiated and led GrooverUI from zero to a shared, token-based design system — spanning web and mobile — for Groover's multilingual marketplace serving 50K+ artists and 3,500+ curators. It's now the foundation every feature ships from.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ═══ 01 · CONTEXT ═══ -->
    <section class="gv-section">
      <div class="container">
        <span class="gv-label">Context</span>
        <h2>It had been tried before. It hadn't worked.</h2>
        <p>
          Before I joined, two previous attempts at a design system had stalled — once as an engineering-only effort with no design input, and once as a Figma library that never made it into production. Components were duplicated across repos, styles drifted between features, and mobile was an afterthought bolted onto desktop layouts.
        </p>
        <p>
          It was clear that the problem wasn't talent or tooling — it was approach. A design system couldn't be a side project. It had to ship incrementally, tied to real feature work, with buy-in from both design and engineering from day one.
        </p>
        <div class="gv-carousel">
          <div class="gv-carousel-track">
            <div class="gv-carousel-slide"><img src="/images/work/grooverui/placeholder.svg" alt="Before state — fragmented UI across Groover's product" width="600" height="400" /></div>
            <div class="gv-carousel-slide"><img src="/images/work/grooverui/placeholder.svg" alt="Inconsistent component usage across flows" width="600" height="400" /></div>
            <div class="gv-carousel-slide"><img src="/images/work/grooverui/placeholder.svg" alt="Duplicated styles across repositories" width="600" height="400" /></div>
          </div>
          <div class="gv-carousel-nav">
            <button class="gv-carousel-dot active" aria-label="Slide 1"></button>
            <button class="gv-carousel-dot" aria-label="Slide 2"></button>
            <button class="gv-carousel-dot" aria-label="Slide 3"></button>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ═══ 02 · APPROACH ═══ -->
    <section class="gv-section">
      <div class="container">
        <span class="gv-label">Approach</span>
        <h2>Incremental by design — not all at once</h2>
        <p>
          Past attempts failed because they tried to systematize everything upfront. I took the opposite approach: ship components only when a feature needs them, then generalize.
        </p>
        <ol class="gv-numbered-list">
          <li>
            <span class="gv-number">1</span>
            <div>
              <strong>Start with what ships next.</strong>
              <p>The first sprint of GrooverUI wasn't a component audit — it was the Spark sign-up redesign. Every token and component was born from a real shipping context, not a theoretical backlog.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="gv-number">2</span>
            <div>
              <strong>Formalize in Figma, validate in Storybook.</strong>
              <p>Every component exists as a Figma variant and a Storybook story. Designers use the library; engineers reference the stories. Neither source drifts because both are part of the same PR review cycle.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="gv-number">3</span>
            <div>
              <strong>Expand only when friction appears.</strong>
              <p>New patterns are added when the team encounters repeated inconsistency — not when someone imagines a future need. This kept the system lean and adoption high.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ═══ 03 · THE SYSTEM ═══ -->
    <section class="gv-section">
      <div class="container">
        <span class="gv-label">The System</span>
        <h2>Tokens first. Components next. Patterns last.</h2>
        <p>
          GrooverUI is built in three layers. Tokens define the visual language — color, type, spacing. Components are the reusable building blocks. Patterns are the composed layouts that tie everything together for specific flows.
        </p>
        <div class="gv-carousel">
          <div class="gv-carousel-track">
            <div class="gv-carousel-slide"><img src="/images/work/grooverui/placeholder.svg" alt="GrooverUI token system — color, type, spacing" width="600" height="400" /></div>
            <div class="gv-carousel-slide"><img src="/images/work/grooverui/placeholder.svg" alt="GrooverUI components — buttons, inputs, chips" width="600" height="400" /></div>
            <div class="gv-carousel-slide"><img src="/images/work/grooverui/placeholder.svg" alt="GrooverUI composed patterns" width="600" height="400" /></div>
          </div>
          <div class="gv-carousel-nav">
            <button class="gv-carousel-dot active" aria-label="Slide 1"></button>
            <button class="gv-carousel-dot" aria-label="Slide 2"></button>
            <button class="gv-carousel-dot" aria-label="Slide 3"></button>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ═══ 04 · MOBILE-FIRST PATTERNS ═══ -->
    <section class="gv-section">
      <div class="container">
        <span class="gv-label">Mobile-First Patterns</span>
        <h2>Designed for thumbs first.</h2>
        <p>
          Groover's audience is global and increasingly mobile. Every component and pattern is designed mobile-first — responsive type scales across three breakpoints, bottom sheets instead of modals on small screens, and touch targets that exceed accessibility minimums.
        </p>
        <div class="gv-carousel">
          <div class="gv-carousel-track">
            <div class="gv-carousel-slide"><img src="/images/work/grooverui/placeholder.svg" alt="Responsive type scale across three breakpoints" width="600" height="400" /></div>
            <div class="gv-carousel-slide"><img src="/images/work/grooverui/placeholder.svg" alt="Bottom sheet pattern on mobile" width="600" height="400" /></div>
            <div class="gv-carousel-slide"><img src="/images/work/grooverui/placeholder.svg" alt="Touch target sizing and accessibility" width="600" height="400" /></div>
          </div>
          <div class="gv-carousel-nav">
            <button class="gv-carousel-dot active" aria-label="Slide 1"></button>
            <button class="gv-carousel-dot" aria-label="Slide 2"></button>
            <button class="gv-carousel-dot" aria-label="Slide 3"></button>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ═══ 05 · IMPACT ═══ -->
    <section class="gv-section gv-impact">
      <div class="container">
        <span class="gv-label">Impact</span>
        <div class="gv-stats-grid">
          <div class="gv-stat-card">
            <span class="gv-stat-number">20+</span>
            <p>Components shipped to production across web and mobile</p>
          </div>
          <div class="gv-stat-card">
            <span class="gv-stat-number">6</span>
            <p>Core flows migrated to GrooverUI in the first two quarters</p>
          </div>
          <div class="gv-stat-card">
            <span class="gv-stat-number">3</span>
            <p>Breakpoints in the responsive type scale — mobile, tablet, desktop</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ═══ 06 · TIMELINE ═══ -->
    <section class="gv-section">
      <div class="container">
        <span class="gv-label">How It Evolved</span>
        <h2>From audit to OKR</h2>
        <div class="gv-timeline">
          <div class="gv-timeline-item">
            <span class="gv-timeline-date">Q3 2023</span>
            <p>Joined Groover. Conducted full UI audit — catalogued 40+ inconsistent patterns across 12 flows.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="gv-timeline-item">
            <span class="gv-timeline-date">Q4 2023</span>
            <p>Shipped GrooverUI V1 alongside the Spark sign-up redesign. First 8 components in Figma + Storybook.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="gv-timeline-item">
            <span class="gv-timeline-date">Q1 2024</span>
            <p>Expanded to 15+ components. Migrated Track Form and Catalog flows. Responsive type scale finalized.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="gv-timeline-item">
            <span class="gv-timeline-date">Q2 2024</span>
            <p>Design system adopted as a formal OKR metric. Bottom sheet pattern shipped for all mobile flows.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="gv-timeline-item">
            <span class="gv-timeline-date">2025</span>
            <p>V2 expansion — FigmaMake + AI integration, 20+ components, dark mode token layer in progress.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ═══ 07 · REFLECTIONS ═══ -->
    <section class="gv-section">
      <div class="container">
        <span class="gv-label">Reflections</span>
        <h2>What I'd tell the next person</h2>
        <div class="gv-reflections-grid">
          <div class="gv-reflection-card">
            <h3>Ship with features, not before them.</h3>
            <p>A design system that launches as a standalone initiative will stall. Tie every component to a real deadline and a real user flow.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="gv-reflection-card">
            <h3>Naming is half the work.</h3>
            <p>If designers and engineers can't agree on what to call something, they'll never agree on how to use it. Invest early in shared vocabulary.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="gv-reflection-card">
            <h3>Adoption beats coverage.</h3>
            <p>10 components used everywhere are worth more than 50 components used sometimes. Optimize for adoption, not completeness.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ═══ BACK LINK ═══ -->
    <nav class="gv-section gv-back" aria-label="Back to work">
      <div class="container">
        <a href="/work" class="gv-back-link">&larr; All Projects</a>
      </div>
    </nav>

  </div>
</Base>

<script>
  document.querySelectorAll('.gv-carousel').forEach((carousel) => {
    const track = carousel.querySelector('.gv-carousel-track');
    const dots = carousel.querySelectorAll('.gv-carousel-dot');
    if (!track || !dots.length) return;

    dots.forEach((dot, i) => {
      dot.addEventListener('click', () => {
        const slide = track.children[i] as HTMLElement;
        track.scrollTo({ left: slide.offsetLeft, behavior: 'smooth' });
      });
    });

    let ticking = false;
    track.addEventListener('scroll', () => {
      if (ticking) return;
      ticking = true;
      requestAnimationFrame(() => {
        const scrollLeft = track.scrollLeft;
        const slideWidth = (track.children[0] as HTMLElement).offsetWidth;
        const active = Math.round(scrollLeft / slideWidth);
        dots.forEach((d, i) => d.classList.toggle('active', i === active));
        ticking = false;
      });
    });
  });
</script>

<style>
  /* ── Dark-theme scoping ── */
  :global(body):has(.grooverui-page) {
    background-color: var(--color-bg);
  }

  .grooverui-page {
    --cs-accent: #FF5C2B;
    --cs-bg: #0c0c0c;
    --cs-surface-1: #131313;
    --cs-surface-2: #1a1a1a;
    --cs-surface-3: #212121;
    --cs-border: rgba(255,255,255,0.07);
    --cs-text: #d8d8d8;
    --cs-text-sub: #909090;
    --cs-text-muted: #606060;
    --cs-green: #4ade80;
  }

  /* ── Hero ── */
  .gv-hero {
    background: var(--cs-bg);
    overflow: hidden;
    aspect-ratio: 21 / 7;
  }

  .gv-hero-img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    display: block;
    object-fit: cover;
    object-position: center top;
  }

  /* ── Shared section ── */
  .gv-section {
    padding-block: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .gv-section .container {
    max-width: 60rem;
  }

  .gv-label {
    display: block;
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--cs-accent);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .gv-section h2 {
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2.25rem);
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
    line-height: 1.2;
  }

  .gv-section p {
    color: #44403c;
    line-height: 1.8;
    max-width: 65ch;
  }

  .gv-section p + p {
    margin-top: var(--space-sm);
  }

  /* ── Intro ── */
  .gv-intro {
    padding-block: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .gv-intro-headline {
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 2.75rem);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .gv-intro-body {
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  /* ── Carousel ── */
  .gv-carousel {
    margin-top: var(--space-lg);
    position: relative;
  }

  .gv-carousel-track {
    display: flex;
    overflow-x: auto;
    scroll-snap-type: x mandatory;
    scroll-behavior: smooth;
    -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch;
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    gap: 0;
    scrollbar-width: none;
  }

  .gv-carousel-track::-webkit-scrollbar {
    display: none;
  }

  .gv-carousel-slide {
    flex: 0 0 100%;
    scroll-snap-align: start;
    background: var(--cs-surface-1);
  }

  .gv-carousel-slide img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
  }

  .gv-carousel-nav {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    margin-top: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .gv-carousel-dot {
    width: 8px;
    height: 8px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    border: none;
    padding: 0;
    cursor: pointer;
    background: var(--color-border);
    transition: background 0.2s ease;
  }

  .gv-carousel-dot.active {
    background: var(--cs-accent);
  }

  /* ── Numbered list ── */
  .gv-numbered-list {
    margin-top: var(--space-lg);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .gv-numbered-list li {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
    align-items: flex-start;
  }

  .gv-number {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 2rem;
    height: 2rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--cs-accent);
    color: #fff;
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-top: 0.125rem;
  }

  .gv-numbered-list strong {
    display: block;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .gv-numbered-list p {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
  }

  /* ── Stats ── */
  .gv-impact .container {
    max-width: 60rem;
  }

  .gv-stats-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
    margin-top: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .gv-stat-card {
    background: var(--cs-surface-1);
    border: 1px solid var(--cs-border);
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .gv-stat-number {
    display: block;
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 3.5rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--cs-accent);
    line-height: 1;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);
  }

  .gv-stat-card p {
    color: var(--cs-text-sub);
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    max-width: none;
    margin-inline: auto;
  }

  /* ── Timeline ── */
  .gv-timeline {
    margin-top: var(--space-lg);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
  }

  .gv-timeline-item {
    padding: var(--space-md) 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.25rem;
  }

  .gv-timeline-item:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .gv-timeline-date {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--cs-accent);
  }

  .gv-timeline-item p {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
  }

  /* ── Reflections ── */
  .gv-reflections-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
    margin-top: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .gv-reflection-card {
    padding: var(--space-md);
    background: var(--color-surface, #ffffff);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
  }

  .gv-reflection-card h3 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-bottom: 0.375rem;
  }

  .gv-reflection-card p {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  /* ── Back ── */
  .gv-back {
  }

  .gv-back .container {
    max-width: 60rem;
  }

  .gv-back-link {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.5em;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--cs-accent);
    transition: gap 0.2s ease;
  }

  .gv-back-link:hover {
    gap: 0.75em;
  }

  /* ── Responsive ── */
  @media (min-width: 48rem) {
    .gv-section .container,
    .gv-back .container {
      padding-inline: var(--space-lg);
    }

    .gv-stats-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    }

    .gv-reflections-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    }

    .gv-section {
      padding-block: var(--space-xl);
    }
  }

</style>
